  "aiDescription": "product_type: Vertical suspended textile panel system; structural_geometry: Single or multi-layered woven fabric sheet hanging vertically with induced continuous folds extending from the top header to the bottom hem; header_attachment: Top edge structured with specific construction (e.g., sewn pleats, metal grommets, rod pocket, or S-curve tape) to connect to suspension hardware and define fold volume; fabric_appearance: Woven textile construction with visible thread structure and surface texture ranging from smooth and uniform to fibrous and tactile; visible_hardware: Horizontal support element (decorative cylindrical rod with rings or low-profile track with gliders) mounted above the opening; stacking_behavior: Retracts horizontally, compressing into dense, vertical fabric columns positioned at the outer edges of the opening; drape_character: Fabric falls under gravity into vertical columns; fold rigidity, depth, and fluidity are determined by the combined weight and stiffness of the face fabric and any applied lining layers; edges_and_details: Bottom and vertical side edges are finished with sewn hems; top edge defined by the selected header construction style",
